{"id":354468,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bradley_Wiggins","text":"Sir Bradley Marc Wiggins, CBE (born 28 April 1980) is a British cyclist. He was born in Ghent, Belgium. He grew up in Kilburn and Maida Vale, London. His mother Linda is English; his father was Australian cyclist Gary Wiggins (1952-2008).\nWiggins won a bronze medal at the 2000 Summer Olympics, a gold medal, silver medal and bronze medal at the 2004 Summer Olympics, two gold medals at the 2008 Summer Olympics and a gold medal at the 2012 Summer Olympics. He won the 2012 Tour de France.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Order_of_the_British_Empire","surface_form":"CBE","offset":26},{"uri":"British_people","surface_form":"British","offset":56},{"uri":"Cyclist","surface_form":"cyclist","offset":64},{"uri":"Ghent","surface_form":"Ghent","offset":88},{"uri":"Belgium","surface_form":"Belgium","offset":95},{"uri":"Kilburn%2C_London","surface_form":"Kilburn","offset":118},{"uri":"Maida_Vale","surface_form":"Maida Vale","offset":130},{"uri":"London","surface_form":"London","offset":142},{"uri":"English_people","surface_form":"English","offset":170},{"uri":"Australia","surface_form":"Australia","offset":194},{"uri":"Gary_Wiggins","surface_form":"Gary Wiggins","offset":213},{"uri":"Bronze_medal","surface_form":"bronze medal","offset":253},{"uri":"2000_Summer_Olympics","surface_form":"2000 Summer Olympics","offset":273},{"uri":"Gold_medal","surface_form":"gold medal","offset":297},{"uri":"Silver_medal","surface_form":"silver medal","offset":309},{"uri":"2004_Summer_Olympics","surface_form":"2004 Summer Olympics","offset":346},{"uri":"2008_Summer_Olympics","surface_form":"2008 Summer Olympics","offset":391},{"uri":"2012_Summer_Olympics","surface_form":"2012 Summer Olympics","offset":436},{"uri":"Tour_de_France","surface_form":"Tour de France","offset":474}]}